'''''Michael Jordan in Flight''''' is a [[1993 in video gaming|1993]] [[computer game|computer]] [[basketball]] game for [[MS-DOS]]. It was developed by [[Electronic Arts]] and [[video game publisher|published]] by [[Dro Soft]] and is endorsed by [[Michael Jordan]] although it has no [[NBA]] licensed players or teams<ref>[http://www.mobygames.com/game/dos/michael-jordan-in-flight Michael Jordan in Flight] at Moby Games</ref>.

== Gameplay ==

The game featured a three-a-side basketball match, and was the first basketball simulator to include graphics (players and court). The camera is a 3D camera, with zoom and includes some filmed scenes of [[Michael Jordan]]. The game is developed in a court surrounded by nothing (even no crowd although you can hear them clapping sometimes)<ref>[http://atarimagazines.planetmirror.com/compute/issue158/144_Michael_Jordan_in_Fl.php Michael Jordan in Flight] COMPUTE! issue 158 / november 1993 / page 144</ref>.

